    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_1101204683" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1101204683" />
    <a title="Euthimia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36746615-euthimia"><img alt="Euthimia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1489428255p2/36746615.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1101204683?book_show_action=true">Nov 08, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Euthimia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Euthimia" href="/user/show/36746615-euthimia">Euthimia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1101204683" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6768714840337673504">I don&apos;t know why it seems that more people are not reading this story, it is awesome! It is shocking, it gives you chills, and the ending is so unexpected! What more could you want in a short story? The first time I read it I had to read it over and over again.</span>
